Creating a New Facade Component

A facade is a `.tid` file that composes mixins into a self-contained component with a `\parameters` API and `$slot`/`$fill` customization points.

Step-by-step process:

1. Create the tiddler file in the components plugin directory
2. Define parameters, import mixins, define rrc0/rrc1 functions
3. Add the render loop (transclude core/menu or inline)
4. Add CSS (class-prefixed stylesheet)
5. Restart the wiki server (new .tid files require restart)

Skeleton for a new facade (using core/menu):

```
code-body: yes
title: $:/plugins/rimir/components/myfacade
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

\parameters (elements:"", selection:"multi", state:"", instid:"")

\import $:/plugins/rimir/components/core/mixins/utils $:/plugins/rimir/components/core/mixins/bytype/visibility-delegate $:/plugins/rimir/components/core/mixins/bytype/class-delegate $:/plugins/rimir/components/core/mixins/bytype/view-delegate $:/plugins/rimir/components/core/mixins/bytype/click-delegate $:/plugins/rimir/components/core/mixins/state-handling

<!-- State setup -->
\function rrc1.state.prefix() [<state>!is[blank]]~[[$:/state/rimir/components/myfacade]]
\function rrc1.uid() [<instid>!is[blank]]~[<qualify>]
\function rrc1.sync.tiddler() [function[rrc1.state.tiddler],[],<rrc1.uid>]
\function rrc1.sync.field() text

<!-- Model: what elements and what types -->
\function rrc0.elems() [subfilter<elements>]
\function rrc0.elem-type(element) selector

<!-- Selection check -->
\function rrc1.elem-selected(tiddler, field, element, yes, no) [<tiddler>get<field>enlist-input[]match<element>then<yes>else<no>]
\function rrc1.elem-add-class(element) [function[rrc1.sync.tiddler]]:map[function[rrc1.elem-selected],<currentTiddler>,<rrc1.sync.field>,<element>,[selected]]

<!-- Click handler -->
\procedure rrc1.elem-clicked(element, modifier, relative-coords)
<$let st={{{[function[rrc1.sync.tiddler]]}}} sf={{{[<rrc1.sync.field>]}}}><$rrcu.ac.sync-with-list tiddler=<<st>> field=<<sf>> element=<<element>>/></$let><$slot $name="on-select" element=<<element>> modifier=<<modifier>>/>
\end

<!-- View -->
\procedure rrc1.elem-view:selector(element)
<$slot $name="view" element=<<element>>><<element>></$slot>
\end

<div class="rrc-myfacade">
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/core/menu">
<$fill $name="additional-contents">
  <!-- extra UI like popups, search inputs, etc. -->
</$fill>
</$transclude>
</div>
```

Key decisions when designing a facade:

**Single type vs multi-type?**
- Single type (like pills): all elements behave the same. Use one type code (e.g., `selector`). Simpler — use core/menu.
- Multi-type (like vtabs): elements have different behaviors based on type. Need a `type-fn` parameter and type-specific handlers. May need to inline the render loop for slot support.

**Using core/menu vs inlining?**
- core/menu: simpler, works when `$slot` is inside a procedure that core/menu calls (pills pattern). `$fill` content is found because core/menu is an intermediate tiddler transclusion.
- Inline: necessary when you need body-level `$slot` per type (vtabs pattern). Copy the render loop from core/menu and add `<%if%>` branching with `$slot` calls.

**Selection model?**
- Import `multi-select` mixin for toggle behavior
- Import `single-select` mixin for replace behavior
- Or define custom `rrc1.elem-clicked` for entirely different behavior (e.g., navigate, delete, reorder)

**Visibility?**
- Default: all elements visible
- Override `rrc1.elem-visible(element, element-type)` to return `yes`/`no`
- Or define type-specific `rrc1.elem-visible:<type>` for per-type visibility logic

Adding a new element type to an existing facade:

If extending vtabs with a new type code (e.g., `tog` for toggle):
1. Add click handler: `\procedure rrc1.elem-clicked:tog(element, modifier, relative-coords)`
2. Add `<%elseif [<element-type>match[tog]]%><$slot $name="view-tog" ...>` in the render loop
3. Add CSS: `.rrc-vtabs span[data-elem-type="tog"] { ... }`

Styling guidelines:

- Use class-prefixed CSS: `.rrc-myfacade span.rrc-elem { ... }`
- Never use `@scope` (Chrome-only)
- Never use `!important`
- Use palette colors: `<<colour primary>>`, `<<colour background>>`, `<<colour tag-background>>`, etc.
- Selected elements: `.rrc-myfacade span[data-elem-type].selected { ... }`
- Per-type styles: `.rrc-myfacade span[data-elem-type="mytype"] { ... }`
- Create a stylesheet tiddler tagged `$:/tags/Stylesheet`

Important constraints:

- `code-body: yes` is required on all facade tiddlers (prevents wikitext parsing of the pragma section)
- `\import` must be a single line with all mixin paths space-separated
- State tiddlers are auto-cleaned by TW only if under `$:/state/` or `$:/temp/`
- The `<qualify>` macro generates a unique ID per transclusion call stack — use it for `instid` default
- Element values must not contain spaces (they are space-separated in lists)
